{"version":1,"ops":[{"type":6,"author":{"id":"02a1aba681ab0b039dd509d683ddfb248d3ca047"},"timestamp":1574267034,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDE1OlVzZXJDb250ZW50RWRpdDMxMjM0Mzk2Mw=="},"target":"ee6a96f9e05a86fb1db2d0b52eeb3b34b8d99d3b051eaf48c463eb0874a458ea","message":"```\nbool NullTest ( struct HashInfo *info ){\n  pfHash hash = info-\u003ehash;\n  unsigned long long h0,\th1;\t\n  hash(NULL,\t0,\t0,\t\u0026h0);\thash(NULL,\t0,\t1,\t\u0026h1);\n  printf(\"nullkey_seed0\\t%llu\\nnullkey_seed1\\t%llu\\n%s\\n\",\th0,\th1,\t\n           h0==h1?\"FAIL\":(h0==0||h1==1?\"Imperfect\":\"PASS\"));\n  return\th0!=h1;\n}  \n```\nclhash\tFAIL\n\nfasthash64\tImperfect\n\nCity64\tImperfect\n\nMUM\tImperfect\n\nxxh3\tImperfect\n\nt1ha2_atonce\tImperfect","files":null},{"type":6,"author":{"id":"02a1aba681ab0b039dd509d683ddfb248d3ca047"},"timestamp":1574267123,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDE1OlVzZXJDb250ZW50RWRpdDMxMjM0NTE4OQ=="},"target":"ee6a96f9e05a86fb1db2d0b52eeb3b34b8d99d3b051eaf48c463eb0874a458ea","message":"```\nbool NullTest ( struct HashInfo *info ){\n  pfHash hash = info-\u003ehash;\n  unsigned long long h0,\th1;\t\n  hash(NULL,\t0,\t0,\t\u0026h0);\t\n  hash(NULL,\t0,\t1,\t\u0026h1);\n  printf(\"nullkey_seed0\\t%llu\\nnullkey_seed1\\t%llu\\n%s\\n\",\th0,\th1,\t\n           h0==h1?\"FAIL\":(h0==0||h1==1?\"Imperfect\":\"PASS\"));\n  return\th0!=h1;\n}  \n```\nclhash\tFAIL\n\nfasthash64\tImperfect\n\nCity64\tImperfect\n\nMUM\tImperfect\n\nxxh3\tImperfect\n\nt1ha2_atonce\tImperfect","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"02a1aba681ab0b039dd509d683ddfb248d3ca047"},"timestamp":1553531267,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQ3NjI3NTA5NQ==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/67#issuecomment-476275095"},"message":"Thanks, but I'm not sure if this is a valid assumption. \nThe return value with a NULL key is undefined, it just should not access out of bounds. Several hashes were OOB.","files":null},{"type":5,"author":{"id":"02a1aba681ab0b039dd509d683ddfb248d3ca047"},"timestamp":1553531273,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOkxhYmVsZWRFdmVudDIyMjcxMzc3Mzk="},"added":["question"],"removed":[]},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"a8f5cc6e3ca5c3c08a52bd4ccf655efd7b4bcadf"},"timestamp":1553548592,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQ3NjM4MDc0MA==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/67#issuecomment-476380740"},"message":"It is just an extreme case test to see if these hashes works properly. if they do memory access, they will fail. xxh3 leaks its key if 0 byte string is processed. some hashes returns zero is key is zero at 0 byte, which is not so good.","files":null},{"type":4,"author":{"id":"a8f5cc6e3ca5c3c08a52bd4ccf655efd7b4bcadf"},"timestamp":1554104008,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDExOkNsb3NlZEV2ZW50MjI0MjM4NTgxNg=="},"status":2},{"type":4,"author":{"id":"02a1aba681ab0b039dd509d683ddfb248d3ca047"},"timestamp":1554117226,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEzOlJlb3BlbmVkRXZlbnQyMjQyOTYzMDQ5"},"status":1},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"173f4fceac25ce053a133bd829b18be7ad10b908"},"timestamp":1554120197,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQ3ODU1MDY0MA==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/67#issuecomment-478550640"},"message":"I think this is valid test, i.e. function should not read data when len = 0.\nOn the other hand \"Imperfect\" criteria is wrong.\n\nFor instance, t1ha2_atonce() pass avalanche test for len=0 (i.e. for seeds only) by https://github.com/demerphq/smhasher.\nBut t1ha2_atonce() intentionally return 0, when both seed and data-length are zero.","files":null},{"type":6,"author":{"id":"173f4fceac25ce053a133bd829b18be7ad10b908"},"timestamp":1554120197,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDE1OlVzZXJDb250ZW50RWRpdDIwMzczNDg5MA=="},"target":"40095b229cadb63f416068f5de387039e6b6aaf0d68e10a7960e1b6a999e8d81","message":"I think this is valid test, i.e. function should not read data when len = 0.\nOn the other hand \"Imperfect\" criteria is wrong.\n\nFor instance, t1ha2_atonce() pass avalanche test for len=0 (i.e. for seeds only) by https://github.com/demerphq/smhasher.\nBut t1ha2_atonce() intentionally return 0, when both seed and data-length are zero (and I think that is normal behavior).","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"0e39a0624a83fb360bfff16b7ac5f230e32c45ed"},"timestamp":1556059527,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQ4NjAwMTU5Nw==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/67#issuecomment-486001597"},"message":"`xxh3` makes a distinction between its secret key, and the `seed`.\nThe secret key is hard to generate, while the `seed` is just a parameter of the function, which could change on a whim.\n\n`xxh3` with a length of `0` and a `seed` of `0` will return `0`, and I also believe this is correct behavior. At least, I received requests for such a feature.\n\nWhen length is `0` but `seed` is not `0`, `xxh3` returns the `seed` (not the secret key !).\nIf this is considered too much of a secret to share, I can change the function so that it returns something less obvious. After all, optimizing the return value for `len==0` is not terribly high in priority order.\nNote that, since it's basically a bijection, whatever its complexity, it will always be possible to brute-force the reverse transformation (given enough resource).","files":null},{"type":6,"author":{"id":"0e39a0624a83fb360bfff16b7ac5f230e32c45ed"},"timestamp":1556059527,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDE1OlVzZXJDb250ZW50RWRpdDIxMzY3MDEyMA=="},"target":"588dd9ba20b78eefd996221c54f4153ae907c61344f37bdef344d26221017beb","message":"`xxh3` makes a distinction between its secret key, and the `seed`.\nThe secret key is hard to generate, while the `seed` is just a parameter of the function, which could change on a whim.\n\n`xxh3` with a length of `0` and a `seed` of `0` will return `0`, and, like @leo-yuriev, I also believe this is correct behavior. At least, I received requests for such a feature.\n\nWhen length is `0` but `seed` is not `0`, `xxh3` returns the `seed` (not the secret key !).\nIf this is considered too much of a secret to share, I can change the function so that it returns something less obvious. After all, optimizing the return value for `len==0` is not terribly high in priority order.\nNote that, since it's basically a bijection, whatever its complexity, it will always be possible to brute-force the reverse transformation (given enough resource).","files":null}]}